<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - INSTALL - AUXILIARY
        COUNTERSHAFT BEARING RACE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT BEARING RACE</title>
        <para>Use a bearing race driver to install the auxiliary countershaft bearing races into their respective bores
            from the rear of the main case (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13032f4">Figure 154</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The bearing races have a slip fit in their respective bores. They should slide or rotate easily
                    into the case bore if they are cocked.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f13032f4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032f4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 154. Installing Auxiliary Countershaft Bearing Races</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
